[
    {
        "index": 1,
        "start_time": 6365,
        "end_time": 8173,
        "text": "When we hear the word radiation,"
    },
    {
        "index": 2,
        "start_time": 8173,
        "end_time": 13120,
        "text": "it&#39;s tempting to picture huge explosions\nand frightening mutations,"
    },
    {
        "index": 3,
        "start_time": 13120,
        "end_time": 14637,
        "text": "but that&#39;s not the full story."
    },
    {
        "index": 4,
        "start_time": 14637,
        "end_time": 16889,
        "text": "Radiation also applies to rainbows"
    },
    {
        "index": 5,
        "start_time": 16889,
        "end_time": 19846,
        "text": "and a doctor examining an x-ray."
    },
    {
        "index": 6,
        "start_time": 19846,
        "end_time": 21846,
        "text": "So what is radiation really,"
    },
    {
        "index": 7,
        "start_time": 21846,
        "end_time": 25092,
        "text": "and how much should we worry\nabout its effects?"
    },
    {
        "index": 8,
        "start_time": 25092,
        "end_time": 28026,
        "text": "The answer begins with understanding\nthat the word radiation"
    },
    {
        "index": 9,
        "start_time": 28026,
        "end_time": 31627,
        "text": "describes two very different \nscientific phenomena:"
    },
    {
        "index": 10,
        "start_time": 31627,
        "end_time": 33626,
        "text": "electromagnetic radiation"
    },
    {
        "index": 11,
        "start_time": 33626,
        "end_time": 36202,
        "text": "and nuclear radiation."
    },
    {
        "index": 12,
        "start_time": 36202,
        "end_time": 39642,
        "text": "Electromagnetic radiation is pure energy"
    },
    {
        "index": 13,
        "start_time": 39642,
        "end_time": 43638,
        "text": "consisting of interacting electrical\nand magnetic waves"
    },
    {
        "index": 14,
        "start_time": 43638,
        "end_time": 46146,
        "text": "oscillating through space."
    },
    {
        "index": 15,
        "start_time": 46146,
        "end_time": 47847,
        "text": "As these waves oscillate faster,"
    },
    {
        "index": 16,
        "start_time": 47847,
        "end_time": 50488,
        "text": "they scale up in energy."
    },
    {
        "index": 17,
        "start_time": 50488,
        "end_time": 53069,
        "text": "At the lower end of the spectrum,\nthere&#39;s radio,"
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "start_time": 53069,
        "end_time": 53879,
        "text": "infrared,"
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "start_time": 53879,
        "end_time": 56376,
        "text": "and visible light."
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "start_time": 56376,
        "end_time": 58279,
        "text": "At the higher end are ultraviolet,"
    },
    {
        "index": 21,
        "start_time": 58279,
        "end_time": 59213,
        "text": "X-ray,"
    },
    {
        "index": 22,
        "start_time": 59213,
        "end_time": 60962,
        "text": "and gamma rays."
    },
    {
        "index": 23,
        "start_time": 60962,
        "end_time": 66109,
        "text": "Modern society is shaped by sending\nand detecting electromagnetic radiation."
    },
    {
        "index": 24,
        "start_time": 66109,
        "end_time": 70089,
        "text": "We might download an email to our phone\nvia radio waves"
    },
    {
        "index": 25,
        "start_time": 70089,
        "end_time": 72449,
        "text": "to open an image of an X-ray print,"
    },
    {
        "index": 26,
        "start_time": 72449,
        "end_time": 76720,
        "text": "which we can see because our screen\nemits visible light."
    },
    {
        "index": 27,
        "start_time": 76720,
        "end_time": 78941,
        "text": "Nuclear radiation, on the other hand,"
    },
    {
        "index": 28,
        "start_time": 78941,
        "end_time": 81230,
        "text": "originates in the atomic nucleus,"
    },
    {
        "index": 29,
        "start_time": 81230,
        "end_time": 85710,
        "text": "where protons repel each other\ndue to their mutually positive charges."
    },
    {
        "index": 30,
        "start_time": 85710,
        "end_time": 88710,
        "text": "A phenomenon known as\nthe strong nuclear force"
    },
    {
        "index": 31,
        "start_time": 88710,
        "end_time": 91402,
        "text": "struggles to overcome this repulsion"
    },
    {
        "index": 32,
        "start_time": 91402,
        "end_time": 93917,
        "text": "and keep the nucleus intact."
    },
    {
        "index": 33,
        "start_time": 93917,
        "end_time": 97454,
        "text": "However, some combinations\nof protons and neutrons,"
    },
    {
        "index": 34,
        "start_time": 97454,
        "end_time": 98964,
        "text": "known as isotopes,"
    },
    {
        "index": 35,
        "start_time": 98964,
        "end_time": 100990,
        "text": "remain unstable,"
    },
    {
        "index": 36,
        "start_time": 100990,
        "end_time": 103276,
        "text": "or radioactive."
    },
    {
        "index": 37,
        "start_time": 103276,
        "end_time": 106110,
        "text": "They will randomly eject matter\nand\/or energy,"
    },
    {
        "index": 38,
        "start_time": 106110,
        "end_time": 108083,
        "text": "known as nuclear radiation,"
    },
    {
        "index": 39,
        "start_time": 108083,
        "end_time": 110399,
        "text": "to achieve greater stability."
    },
    {
        "index": 40,
        "start_time": 110399,
        "end_time": 114170,
        "text": "Nuclear radiation comes from natural\nsources, like radon,"
    },
    {
        "index": 41,
        "start_time": 114170,
        "end_time": 116509,
        "text": "a gas which seeps up from the ground."
    },
    {
        "index": 42,
        "start_time": 116509,
        "end_time": 120146,
        "text": "We also refine naturally occurring\nradioactive ores"
    },
    {
        "index": 43,
        "start_time": 120146,
        "end_time": 122789,
        "text": "to fuel nuclear power plants."
    },
    {
        "index": 44,
        "start_time": 122789,
        "end_time": 128159,
        "text": "Even bananas contain trace amounts\nof a radioactive potassium isotope."
    },
    {
        "index": 45,
        "start_time": 128159,
        "end_time": 130576,
        "text": "So if we live in a world of radiation,"
    },
    {
        "index": 46,
        "start_time": 130576,
        "end_time": 133603,
        "text": "how can we escape its dangerous effects?"
    },
    {
        "index": 47,
        "start_time": 133603,
        "end_time": 137332,
        "text": "To start, not all radiation is hazardous."
    },
    {
        "index": 48,
        "start_time": 137332,
        "end_time": 143361,
        "text": "Radiation becomes risky when it rips\natoms&#39; electrons away upon impact,"
    },
    {
        "index": 49,
        "start_time": 143361,
        "end_time": 146000,
        "text": "a process that can damage DNA."
    },
    {
        "index": 50,
        "start_time": 146000,
        "end_time": 148636,
        "text": "This is known as ionizing radiation"
    },
    {
        "index": 51,
        "start_time": 148636,
        "end_time": 153460,
        "text": "because an atom that has lost\nor gained electrons is called an ion."
    },
    {
        "index": 52,
        "start_time": 153460,
        "end_time": 156012,
        "text": "All nuclear radiation is ionizing,"
    },
    {
        "index": 53,
        "start_time": 156012,
        "end_time": 160640,
        "text": "while only the highest energy \nelectromagnetic radiation is."
    },
    {
        "index": 54,
        "start_time": 160640,
        "end_time": 161987,
        "text": "That includes gamma rays,"
    },
    {
        "index": 55,
        "start_time": 161987,
        "end_time": 163073,
        "text": "X-rays,"
    },
    {
        "index": 56,
        "start_time": 163073,
        "end_time": 166078,
        "text": "and the high-energy end of ultraviolet."
    },
    {
        "index": 57,
        "start_time": 166078,
        "end_time": 168850,
        "text": "That&#39;s why as an extra precaution\nduring X-rays,"
    },
    {
        "index": 58,
        "start_time": 168850,
        "end_time": 173059,
        "text": "doctors shield body parts \nthey don&#39;t need to examine,"
    },
    {
        "index": 59,
        "start_time": 173059,
        "end_time": 175929,
        "text": "and why beach-goers use sunscreen."
    },
    {
        "index": 60,
        "start_time": 175929,
        "end_time": 181086,
        "text": "In comparison, cell phones and microwaves\noperate at the lower end of the spectrum,"
    },
    {
        "index": 61,
        "start_time": 181086,
        "end_time": 184942,
        "text": "so there is no risk of ionizing radiation\nfrom their use."
    },
    {
        "index": 62,
        "start_time": 184942,
        "end_time": 188709,
        "text": "The biggest health risk occurs\nwhen lots of ionizing radiation"
    },
    {
        "index": 63,
        "start_time": 188709,
        "end_time": 191548,
        "text": "hits us in a short time period,"
    },
    {
        "index": 64,
        "start_time": 191548,
        "end_time": 194440,
        "text": "also known as an acute exposure."
    },
    {
        "index": 65,
        "start_time": 194440,
        "end_time": 199233,
        "text": "Acute exposures overwhelm the body&#39;s\nnatural ability to repair the damage."
    },
    {
        "index": 66,
        "start_time": 199233,
        "end_time": 200610,
        "text": "This can trigger cancers,"
    },
    {
        "index": 67,
        "start_time": 200610,
        "end_time": 202126,
        "text": "cellular dysfunction,"
    },
    {
        "index": 68,
        "start_time": 202126,
        "end_time": 204638,
        "text": "and potentially even death."
    },
    {
        "index": 69,
        "start_time": 204638,
        "end_time": 207154,
        "text": "Fortunately, acute exposures are rare,"
    },
    {
        "index": 70,
        "start_time": 207154,
        "end_time": 211562,
        "text": "but we are exposed daily to lower levels\nof ionizing radiation"
    },
    {
        "index": 71,
        "start_time": 211562,
        "end_time": 215324,
        "text": "from both natural and man-made sources."
    },
    {
        "index": 72,
        "start_time": 215324,
        "end_time": 218842,
        "text": "Scientists have a harder time quantifying\nthese risks."
    },
    {
        "index": 73,
        "start_time": 218842,
        "end_time": 222663,
        "text": "Your body often repairs damage\nfrom small amounts ionizing radiation,"
    },
    {
        "index": 74,
        "start_time": 222663,
        "end_time": 223856,
        "text": "and if it can&#39;t,"
    },
    {
        "index": 75,
        "start_time": 223856,
        "end_time": 228781,
        "text": "the results of damage may not manifest\nfor a decade or more."
    },
    {
        "index": 76,
        "start_time": 228781,
        "end_time": 231873,
        "text": "One way scientists compare ionizing\nradiation exposure"
    },
    {
        "index": 77,
        "start_time": 231873,
        "end_time": 233967,
        "text": "is a unit called the sievert."
    },
    {
        "index": 78,
        "start_time": 233967,
        "end_time": 239376,
        "text": "An acute exposure to one sievert\nwill probably cause nausea within hours,"
    },
    {
        "index": 79,
        "start_time": 239376,
        "end_time": 242175,
        "text": "and four sieverts could be fatal."
    },
    {
        "index": 80,
        "start_time": 242175,
        "end_time": 246042,
        "text": "However, our normal daily exposures\nare far lower."
    },
    {
        "index": 81,
        "start_time": 246042,
        "end_time": 250160,
        "text": "The average person receives \n6.2 millisieverts of radiation"
    },
    {
        "index": 82,
        "start_time": 250160,
        "end_time": 252726,
        "text": "from all sources annually,"
    },
    {
        "index": 83,
        "start_time": 252726,
        "end_time": 255107,
        "text": "around a third due to radon."
    },
    {
        "index": 84,
        "start_time": 255107,
        "end_time": 257518,
        "text": "At only five microsieverts each,"
    },
    {
        "index": 85,
        "start_time": 257518,
        "end_time": 260583,
        "text": "you&#39;d need to get more \nthan 1200 dental X-rays"
    },
    {
        "index": 86,
        "start_time": 260583,
        "end_time": 262862,
        "text": "to rack up your annual dosage."
    },
    {
        "index": 87,
        "start_time": 262862,
        "end_time": 264475,
        "text": "And remember that banana?"
    },
    {
        "index": 88,
        "start_time": 264475,
        "end_time": 267084,
        "text": "If you could absorb \nall the banana&#39;s radiation,"
    },
    {
        "index": 89,
        "start_time": 267084,
        "end_time": 272455,
        "text": "you&#39;d need around 170 a day\nto hit your annual dosage."
    },
    {
        "index": 90,
        "start_time": 272455,
        "end_time": 274580,
        "text": "We live in a world of radiation."
    },
    {
        "index": 91,
        "start_time": 274580,
        "end_time": 278318,
        "text": "However, much of that radiation\nis non-ionizing."
    },
    {
        "index": 92,
        "start_time": 278318,
        "end_time": 280316,
        "text": "For the remainder that is ionizing,"
    },
    {
        "index": 93,
        "start_time": 280316,
        "end_time": 282540,
        "text": "our exposures are usually low,"
    },
    {
        "index": 94,
        "start_time": 282540,
        "end_time": 285269,
        "text": "and choices like getting your home\ntested for radon"
    },
    {
        "index": 95,
        "start_time": 285269,
        "end_time": 287007,
        "text": "and wearing sunscreen"
    },
    {
        "index": 96,
        "start_time": 287007,
        "end_time": 290106,
        "text": "can help reduce \nthe associated health risks."
    },
    {
        "index": 97,
        "start_time": 290106,
        "end_time": 293222,
        "text": "Marie Curie, \none of the early radiation pioneers,"
    },
    {
        "index": 98,
        "start_time": 293222,
        "end_time": 295541,
        "text": "summed up the challenge as follows:"
    },
    {
        "index": 99,
        "start_time": 295541,
        "end_time": 299976,
        "text": "&quot;Nothing in life is to be feared,\nit is only to be understood."
    },
    {
        "index": 100,
        "start_time": 299976,
        "end_time": 304672,
        "text": "Now is the time to understand more,\nso that we may fear less.&quot;"
    }
]